+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SEvTWVW5emLoWXrivfeiVU","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have completed a thorough exploration of the codebase. Here's my comprehensive report:\n\n## Complete Codebase Analysis\n\n### 1. Full Directory Structure\n\n```\n/workspace/\n├── .eslintrc.cjs                 (ESLint configuration)\n├── .gitignore\n├── .git/                         (Git repository)\n├── package.json                  (NPM configuration)\n├── package-lock.json             (Lock file)\n├── tsconfig.json                 (TypeScript configuration)\n├── vitest.config.ts              (Vitest configuration)\n├── TASK.md                       (Main task description)\n├── phases/                       (12 phase requirement files)\n│   ├── phase-01.md\n│   ├── phase-02.md\n│   ├── phase-03.md\n│   ├── phase-04.md\n│   ├── phase-05.md\n│   ├── phase-06.md\n│   ├── phase-07.md\n│   ├── phase-08.md\n│   ├── phase-09.md\n│   ├── phase-10.md\n│   ├── phase-11.md\n│   └── phase-12.md\n└── src/                          (Source code directory - currently empty)\n    └── .gitkeep\n```\n\n### 2. package.json Contents\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"bench-task-queue\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"description\": \"Task queue marathon benchmark\",\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"build\": \"tsc\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint src/\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest run\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@types/node\": \"^25.2.3\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/parser\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"eslint\": \"^8.56.0\",\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.4.0\",\n    \"@vitest/coverage-v8\": \"^2.0.0\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^2.0.0\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### 3. tsconfig.json Contents\n\n```json\n{\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\n    \"target\": \"ES2022\",\n    \"module\": \"Node16\",\n    \"moduleResolution\": \"Node16\",\n    \"outDir\": \"./dist\",\n    \"rootDir\": \"./src\",\n    \"strict\": true,\n    \"esModuleInterop\": true,\n    \"skipLibCheck\": true,\n    \"forceConsistentCasingInFileNames\": true,\n    \"resolveJsonModule\": true,\n    \"declaration\": true,\n    \"declarationMap\": true,\n    \"sourceMap\": true\n  },\n  \"include\": [\"src/**/*\"],\n  \"exclude\": [\"node_modules\", \"dist\", \"tests\"]\n}\n```\n\n### 4. .eslintrc.cjs (ESLint Configuration)\n\n```javascript\nmodule.exports = {\n  parser: '@typescript-eslint/parser',\n  plugins: ['@typescript-eslint'],\n  extends: ['eslint:recommended', 'plugin:@typescript-eslint/recommended'],\n  parserOptions: {\n    ecmaVersion: 2022,\n    sourceType: 'module',\n  },\n  rules: {\n    '@typescript-eslint/no-unused-vars': ['error', { argsIgnorePattern: '^_', varsIgnorePattern: '^_' }],\n  },\n  env: {\n    node: true,\n    es2022: true,\n  },\n};\n```\n\n### 5. vitest.config.ts (Test Configuration)\n\n```typescript\nimport { defineConfig } from 'vitest/config';\n\nexport default defineConfig({\n  test: {\n    globals: true,\n    testTimeout: 10000,\n  },\n});\n```\n\n### 6. TASK.md (Main Requirements)\n\nThe project is to build a **fully-featured in-memory task queue system** from scratch that evolves through 12 phases. Key points:\n\n- Export main API from `src/index.ts`\n- No external runtime dependencies allowed\n- Write tests as you go\n- Must pass `npm run build` and `npm run lint`\n\nThe system should grow through 12 phases of increasing sophistication, each building on previous work.\n\n### 7. Complete Phase Files\n\n#### **Phase 1: Basic FIFO Queue** (/workspace/phases/phase-01.md)\n\nRequirements:\n- Accept payload, return task object with unique ID, status, and creation timestamp\n- New tasks start in \"pending\" state\n- Retrieve oldest pending task → transition to \"processing\"\n- Return null if no tasks available\n- Way to check pending task count\n\n#### **Phase 2: Named Queues** (/workspace/phases/phase-02.md)\n\nRequirements:\n- Tasks added to specific named queue\n- Default queue when no name given\n- Each queue operates independently\n- Implicit queue creation on first task add\n- List all queue names\n- Backward-compatible with Phase 1\n\n#### **Phase 3: Priority** (/workspace/phases/phase-03.md)\n\nRequirements:\n- Priority 1-10 (1 highest, 10 lowest, default 5)\n- Higher priority (lower number) returned first\n- Same priority = FIFO order\n- Invalid priorities cause error\n- Priority per-queue\n- Task object exposes priority level\n\n#### **Phase 4: Delayed and Scheduled Tasks** (/workspace/phases/phase-04.md)\n\nRequirements:\n- Delay (milliseconds) or specific future time\n- Delayed tasks added immediately but not returned until available\n- Non-delayed tasks preferred over unavailable delayed tasks\n- Multiple simultaneous delayed tasks ordered by: availability time → priority → FIFO\n- Task object indicates availability time\n- Works with named queues\n\n#### **Phase 5: Retry with Backoff** (/workspace/phases/phase-05.md)\n\nRequirements:\n- Mark task as completed or failed\n- Failed tasks auto-retry with delay if retries remaining\n- Exponential backoff: `baseDelay * 2^(attempt - 1)` (1s, 2s, 4s...)\n- Default max retries: 3 (configurable per task)\n- Default base delay: 1000ms (configurable per task)\n- Track attempt count\n- Retried tasks keep original queue and priority\n- Exhausted retries = failed state\n\n#### **Phase 6: Dead Letter Queue** (/workspace/phases/phase-06.md)\n\nRequirements:\n- Move tasks to DLQ when exhausted all retries\n- View all dead-lettered tasks per queue\n- Retain error information and failure count\n- Move dead-lettered task back to original queue\n- Clear all dead-lettered tasks per queue\n- Each queue has independent DLQ\n\n#### **Phase 7: Task Dependencies** (/workspace/phases/phase-07.md)\n\nRequirements:\n- Specify list of task IDs that must complete first\n- Blocked tasks not returned when retrieving\n- Check if blocked tasks unblocked when dependency completes\n- Detect and